modules.description: This module provides serialization and deserialization functions for the `Bitvec.t` type using the Binprot protocol. It includes operations for measuring size, writing and reading values, and defining shape and type-level protocols. These functions support implementing binable interfaces for existing types without redefining their structure, particularly useful when extending types with variant constructors that require custom reading logic.

This module implements serialization and deserialization routines for `Bitvec.t` using the Binprot protocol. It provides functions to measure binary size, write and read values, and define type-level protocols, supporting efficient storage and transmission of bit vectors. Use cases include persisting bit vector data to disk or sending it over a network in a binary format.
